  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Implementation of Social Cohesion Activities in Mayukwayukwa and Meheba Local Integration Sites</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of a larger United Nations - Government of Republic of Zambia (UN - GRZ) Sustainable Resettlement Joint Programme. This falls within the overall programming framework of the UN in Zambia, namely the Zambia-UN Sustainable Development Partnership Framework 2016-2021 that also feeds into the 7th National Development Plan. IOM supports the GRZ to work towards its commitment to improving the lives and rights of locally integrated former refugees living in Zambia. In doing so, this action facilitates and supports local integration of eligible former refugees from Angola and Rwanda, promotes self-reliance, enhances favourable measures for former refugees to access work and engage in income generating activities, promotes social cohesion and peaceful coexistence between the former refugees and host communities, as well as strengthens protection systems for both.</narrative>
  </description>
